# Third-Party Licenses

XtoMarkdown uses the following open source software:

## Pandoc (GPL v2+)

Pandoc is a universal document converter.

- Website: https://pandoc.org/
- Source Code: https://github.com/jgm/pandoc
- License: GNU General Public License v2 or later

Pandoc is called as a separate subprocess and is not linked into this application.
Full license text available in LICENSES/GPL-2.0.txt

## pypandoc (MIT)

Python wrapper for Pandoc.

- Source Code: https://github.com/JessicaTegner/pypandoc
- License: MIT License

Full license text available in LICENSES/MIT-pypandoc.txt

## MarkItDown (MIT)

Microsoft's library for converting documents to Markdown.

- Source Code: https://github.com/microsoft/markitdown
- License: MIT License
- Copyright (c) Microsoft Corporation

Full license text available in LICENSES/MIT-markitdown.txt

## PySide6 (LGPL v3)

Qt for Python - Official Python bindings for Qt.

- Website: https://www.qt.io/qt-for-python
- Source Code: https://code.qt.io/cgit/pyside/pyside-setup.git/
- License: GNU Lesser General Public License v3

Full license text available in LICENSES/LGPL-3.0.txt

## platformdirs (MIT)

Cross-platform directories for application data.

- Source Code: https://github.com/platformdirs/platformdirs
- License: MIT License

Full license text available in LICENSES/MIT-platformdirs.txt

---

Full license texts for all dependencies are available in the LICENSES/ directory.
